Text:
#YolkPop ‚Ä¶ now that I have your attention, it‚Äôs holiday time, my favourite time of the year! This year, I‚Äôm partnering with Egg Farmers of Canada (@eggsoeufs) to celebrate the holiday season and share a recipe using one of my favourite ingredients: Canadian eggs!

As a chef, it‚Äôs a given that I‚Äôll be cooking up a storm for my family and friends at our holiday gatherings, so I want to make it as easy and seamless as possible by prepping what I can ahead of time. That‚Äôs why I‚Äôm sharing my Mushrooms on Toast recipe! It‚Äôs such an easy, but totally delicious side dish, and most of the components can be made ahead of time to ensure your holiday festivities go on without a hitch. Your poached eggs can be made a day ahead and kept
in the fridge in an airtight container! All you have to do before your guests arrive is boil some water and let your eggs come back to life for a few seconds. You‚Äôll have delicious eggs with picture perfect runny yolks. Your mushrooms can also be made a day or two ahead and reheated the day of.

For a more savoury flavour, you can swap the maple syrup for balsamic vinegar and use a bit more butter! Or try both versions of the recipe and report back on which you like better. Head to eggs.ca for the full recipe ‚Ä¶ and don‚Äôt worry, this A+ recipe can be made on your kitchen stovetop, too! #SeasonToShare #ad #EggsAnytime

Title: Mar 15, 2023
Text:
Happy Dietitians Day!
We are so lucky to get to work with amazing RD creators and egg lovers to spread #EggFacts and to help
you eat balanced, delicious meals and snacks that suit your lifestyle!

There is a lot of nutrition misinformation out there, so it‚Äôs best to follow registered dietitians to ensure
you are getting credible, evidence-based nutrition information that you know you can trust! If you‚Äôre
unsure of someone‚Äôs credentials, always look for ‚ÄúDietitian‚Äù, ‚ÄúRegistered Dietitian‚Äù or ‚ÄúRD‚Äù.

Carrie from @walderwellness is a recipe developer and blogger, and she creates delicious and nutritious recipes like this dill-licious pickle salad with eggs.

Sue from @suemahrd is an award-winning media dietitian who shares fun food / nutrition
information to help Canadians eat well and live well!

Jen from @eatsby.jay creates approachable meals & snacks that are quick to prepare and always delicious, with a Middle Eastern twist like this toast with labneh & eggs!

Vanessa from @van_nutritionniste is a content creator and sport enthusiast based in Quebec, and she
has a podcast where she talks about different topics related to health.

Becca from @nutritionjunky specializes in ADHD nutrition and develops delicious recipes like this angel food cake! Fun fact, it‚Äôs light and fluffy and uses 12 egg whites!

Title: Jul 23, 2022
Text:
I always look forward to the weekend - that's when brunch vibes are at an all time high! I am so egg-cited to bring you along to visit one of my favourite brunch spots in Toronto: @kosttoronto! I think most of us can agree that there is one food item that is basically synonymous with brunch - eggs!

The meal just wouldn't be the same without them (and a mimosa or two of course). Kost not only has a variety of egg dishes to choose from, but you'll get to enjoy it while dining on the 44th floor of their rooftop patio poolside overlooking the CN Tower!

Eggs are so versatile in cooking. In any meal from breakfast, lunch, and dinner you can most certainly make the egg a delicious star of the dish. And in this case, brunch at Kost served one dish with the egg poached and the other sunny side up. How do you like your eggs?

‚úÖ Lobster Eggs Benedict - served with two poached eggs, roasted potatoes, crema bearnaise.

‚úÖ Kost Eggs on Rib Hash - roasted potatoes, sunny side up egg, short rib barbacoa, piquillo pepper.

If you're deciding which restaurant to visit for brunch, just remember... eggs with a view! @kosttoronto is the place to be! @eggsoeufs #EggsAnytime #LocalLove #BrunchTimeüç≥
